seller_description.id_description1: I've decided to sell my 2006 Porsche Cayenne Turbo-S. The family is growing, so the car needs to grow, too! I've had it since 2019 and am only the second owner. It's been an amazing car for me in the 6 years that I've had it. Some of the automotive magazines have tagged it as a Future Classic. The original owner traded it back to the dealership where he purchased it, Porsche of North Houston.
seller_description.id_description5: Interior: Havanna beige leather with brushed aluminum accents, full alcantara headliner. Even the grab handles and dashboard are leather. The brushed aluminum accelerator and brake pedals still have the factory-original protective film on them - you can be the first to peel it off if you want.
seller_description.id_description6: 4.5L V8, twin turbo - making 520hp and 530ft/lbs of torque
seller_description.id_description8: 4wd/awd with selectable low-range gearbox and automatic center locking differential
seller_description.id_description9: 6-piston red brake calipers up front with 15" diameter x 1.5" thick rotors
seller_description.id_description10: 4-piston red brake calipers in the rear with 14.1" x 1.1" thick rotors
seller_description.id_description12: 10" X 20" OEM wheels in the rear
seller_description.id_description13: User-adjustable air suspension gives you 8" of height adjustability - from Parking level through Special Terrain height. The system works flawlessly with its on-board air compressor system.
seller_description.id_description14: Bose audio system with factory subwoofer - AM/FM/Satellite radio, CD player, navigation (older tech, but there and functional) - a caveat that the stereo sometimes cuts out in colder temps, so I'd ballpark it as functional approximately 60% of the time. It's mostly just a nuisance when this occurs. Porsche actually makes a new-production version of this exact head unit with modern updates, if you're so inclined to swap it out. Also, xtrons makes a popular aftermarket unit and Cayenne-specific bezel if you wanted to go the aftermarket direction and still have a clean installation - plus, it allows you to add a backup camera.
seller_description.id_description15: Multi-zone climate control including separate rear passenger controls
seller_description.id_description16: Front and rear seats are all heated with infinite temp control - not just a few set switch positions
seller_description.id_description18: User-selectable air-conditioned glove box (OEM feature - not kidding)
seller_description.id_description21: The Turbo-S model of the first-generation Cayenne (955, 2003-2006) was only available in the 2006 model year - and only for a portion of that year, making it extremely limited-production
seller_description.id_description22: Porsche set production at 1,500 cars worldwide, with only 600 sent to the US market
seller_description.id_description23: The 2006 Turbo-S Cayenne was the most powerful mass-production Porsche ever made at that point in time. Only the Carrera GT supercar, produced only from 2003-2006, made more power with its bespoke V10, 605hp engine (approx. $450k in 2006, now ranging from $1.2 - 3.5 million)
seller_description.id_description24: 0-60 mph in 4.8 seconds with a top speed of 167 mph
seller_description.id_description26: Oil change, Mobil 1 full synthetic - May 2025 @ 153,350 mi.
seller_description.id_description27: Rear hatch and hatch glass struts replaced (each has its own pair since they can open separately) - May 2025
seller_description.id_description28: New tires (Pirelli P-Zero in OEM size: 275/40-20) - April 2025
seller_description.id_description29: New TPMS sensors at all 4 wheels - April 2025
seller_description.id_description30: New front brake pads (OEM Pagid pads) - March 2025
seller_description.id_description31: Schrader valves replaced on AC high and low-pressure AC lines, system vacuumed and charged - March 2025
seller_description.id_description33: New windshield wipers front & rear - February 2025
seller_description.id_description34: There is a burgeoning offroad Cayenne scene, in case that interests you - check it out via social media or Google for ideas.
